ENTRY       EC 4.2.1.139                Enzyme
NAME        medicarpin synthase;
            medicarpan synthase;
            7,2'-dihydroxy-4'-methoxyisoflavanol dehydratase;
            2',7-dihydroxy-4'-methoxyisoflavanol dehydratase;
            DMI dehydratase;
            DMID
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Hydro-lyases
SYSNAME     4'-methoxyisoflavan-2',4,7-triol hydro-lyase [(-)-medicarpin-forming]
REACTION    4'-methoxyisoflavan-2',4,7-triol = (-)-medicarpin + H2O [RN:R07738]
ALL_REAC    R07738
SUBSTRATE   4'-methoxyisoflavan-2',4,7-triol
PRODUCT     (-)-medicarpin [CPD:C10503];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
COMMENT     Isolated from the plant Medicago sativa (alfalfa). Catalyses the final step in the biosynthesis of medicarpin, the main pterocarpan phytoalexin in alfalfa.
